               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460817-name-664" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-664" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-664" type="surname" value="TYLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-664" type="given" value="CHARLES JOHN"></interp>CHARLES JOHN TYLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a jeweller, and live in Brick-lane, in the parish of Christchurch, Spitalfields. On Saturday, the 15th of Aug., at one o'clock in the afternoon, I was at dinner in the back room, and had a full view of the shop window—a pane of glass was cracked—I saw the prisoner standing outside the window, with his arm through the pane, which I found was then broken—I instantly ran out—he was running away—I pursued, and saw him drop two brooches—I took hold of him, returned to the spot, and picked up two brooches—those produced are mine, and were safe jost before—I lost a seal, which has not been found—I was foolishly persuaded to let the prisoner go—he came back to the side of the window—I took him, and kept him—I am sure he is the boy.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460817-name-665" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-665" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-665" type="surname" value="CHESTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-665" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS CHESTER</persName>
                  </hi>. My shop is next door to Tyler's. I was standing at the door this afternoon, saw Mr. Tyler run by, and saw the prisoner drop the brooches—I am quite sure of that.</p>
